The paper deals with a problem related to planar graphs and their connectivity, which suggests that it could belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) category. The use of graphs and their components also suggests that it could belong to the data structures (cs.DS) category. The paper also involves combinatorial optimization and graph theory, which could place it in the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) category. The problem of graph morphing involves graph transformations, which could place it in the graph theory (cs.GT) category. Finally, the paper involves algorithms and computational complexity, which could place it in the computational complexity (cs.SI) category.
